3 CHAPTER 13: THE LOUISIANA MONEY TRANSMISSION ACT
4 §1031. Short title
5 This Chapter shall be known as and may be cited as the "Louisiana Money
6 Transmission Act."
7 §1032. Purpose
8 This Chapter is designed to replace the "Sale of Checks and Money
9 Transmission Act" codified at Title 6, Chapter 13, R.S. 6:1031 et seq. It is the intent
10 of the Legislature that the provisions of this Chapter accomplish all of the following:
11 (1) Ensure states can coordinate in all areas of regulation, licensing, and
12 supervision to eliminate unnecessary regulatory burden and more effectively utilize
13 regulatory resources.
14 (2) Protect the Louisiana public from financial crime.
15 (3) Standardize the types of activities that are subject to licensing or
16 otherwise exempt from licensing.
17 (4) Modernize the licensure, supervision, and regulation of multistate money
18 transmission licenses with current safety and soundness requirements to ensure
19 customer funds are protected in an environment that supports innovative and
20 competitive business practices.
